{
    "name": "Undine Hydromancer",
    "type": "creature",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Undine",
            "type": "section",
            "sources": [
                {
                    "type": "source",
                    "name": "Bestiary 2",
                    "link": {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Bestiary 2 pg. 203",
                        "alt": "Bestiary 2 pg. 203",
                        "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq022yq"
                    },
                    "page": 203
                }
            ],
            "html": "Undines are infused with elemental water\u2014the churning power of the briny deep flows through them. These planar scions are often athletic and lithe, but they are easily distracted by auditory sensations because of how much louder and clearer sound rings above the waves.<br/><br/> Undines are perhaps the most settled of all geniekin, often forming communities along the coast or even on the water itself. In the latter case, they prefer to settle in ship-towns that sometimes number dozens of vessels in all shapes and sizes. The undines who fill these communities are similarly diverse, bringing aspects of multiple cultures together to form one whole. Ship-towns are permanent, but fluid\u2014they grow, recede, and migrate constantly as undine families add their ships to or remove them from the flotilla. An undine town like this may remain at sea for years, its residents coming ashore only on rare occasions to collect wood for cookfires or to repair their homes. The paradoxically ever-shifting permanence of these communities reflects the undine virtues of adaptability and freedom, while also maintaining the prime importance of the community.<br/><br/> Undine hydromancers are quite valued on these floating settlements, if only for their ability to create fresh drinking water while adrift on the sea.<br/><br/><b><u><a aonid=\"5\" game-obj=\"Skills\" general=\"true\">Recall Knowledge - Humanoid</a></u> (<u><a aonid=\"14\" game-obj=\"Skills\">Society</a></u>)</b>: DC 15"
        },
        {
            "name": "Geniekin",
            "type": "section",
            "sections": [
                {
                    "name": "Planar Scion",
                    "type": "section",
                    "sections": [
                        {
                            "name": "Related Groups",
                            "type": "section",
                            "sources": [
                                {
                                    "type": "source",
                                    "name": "Bestiary 2",
                                    "link": {
                                        "type": "link",
                                        "name": "Bestiary 2 pg. 200",
                                        "alt": "Bestiary 2 pg. 200",
                                        "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq022yq"
                                    },
                                    "page": 200
                                }
                            ],
                            "html": "<u><a aonid=\"81\" game-obj=\"MonsterFamilies\">Planar Scion</a></u><br/>Many immortals dwell upon the other planes of the Great Beyond. Some are benevolent and kindly, like angels. Others are cruel and destructive, like demons. And some flt roles outside of morality, like psychopomps. It\u2019s far from unheard of that mortals and immortals alike become entangled romantically, and the children of such engagements carry a supernatural element in their bloodlines for generations to follow. After the first generation, this otherworldly influence usually lies dormant, but now and then, the influence can manifest strongly in descendants many years later. These inheritors of extraplanar legacies are known collectively as planar scions."
                        },
                        {
                            "name": "Geniekin on Golarion",
                            "type": "section",
                            "sources": [
                                {
                                    "type": "source",
                                    "name": "Bestiary 2",
                                    "link": {
                                        "type": "link",
                                        "name": "Bestiary 2 pg. 200",
                                        "alt": "Bestiary 2 pg. 200",
                                        "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq022yq"
                                    },
                                    "page": 200
                                }
                            ],
                            "subtype": "sidebar",
                            "sidebar_type": "locations",
                            "sidebar_heading": "Locations",
                            "image": {
                                "type": "image",
                                "name": "Locations",
                                "image": "Sidebar_3_Locations.png"
                            },
                            "html": "While most geniekin planar scions live on their genie parent's ancestral plane, rare fonts of elemental power or genie activity sometimes give rise to geniekin on Golarion. By far, geniekin are most commonly found in Katapesh, as genies are more prevalent there than other regions due to the influence of genie binders."
                        },
                        {
                            "name": "Geniekin Parentage",
                            "type": "section",
                            "sources": [
                                {
                                    "type": "source",
                                    "name": "Bestiary 2",
                                    "link": {
                                        "type": "link",
                                        "name": "Bestiary 2 pg. 200",
                                        "alt": "Bestiary 2 pg. 200",
                                        "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq022yq"
                                    },
                                    "page": 200
                                }
                            ],
                            "subtype": "sidebar",
                            "sidebar_type": "additional_lore",
                            "sidebar_heading": "Additional Lore",
                            "image": {
                                "type": "image",
                                "name": "Additional Lore",
                                "image": "Sidebar_2_AdditionalLore.png"
                            },
                            "html": "Planar scions from the elemental planes are known as geniekin because they are overwhelmingly born from couplings between mortals and genies: <a aonid=\"759\" game-obj=\"Monsters\">ifrits</a> are born of <a aonid=\"214\" game-obj=\"Monsters\">efreeti</a>, <a aonid=\"760\" game-obj=\"Monsters\">oreads</a> of <a aonid=\"213\" game-obj=\"Monsters\">shaitans</a>, <a aonid=\"761\" game-obj=\"Monsters\">sulis</a> of <a aonid=\"211\" game-obj=\"Monsters\">jann</a>, <a aonid=\"762\" game-obj=\"Monsters\">sylphs</a> of <a aonid=\"212\" game-obj=\"Monsters\">djinn</a>, and <a aonid=\"763\" game-obj=\"Monsters\">undines</a> of <a aonid=\"215\" game-obj=\"Monsters\">marids</a>. Despite this distinguished ancestry, geniekin do not display most of their parents' exceptional talents, such as their ability to grant wishes."
                        }
                    ],
                    "sources": [
                        {
                            "type": "source",
                            "name": "Bestiary 2",
                            "link": {
                                "type": "link",
                                "name": "Bestiary 2 pg. 200",
                                "alt": "Bestiary 2 pg. 200",
                                "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq022yq"
                            },
                            "page": 200
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ],
            "sources": [
                {
                    "type": "source",
                    "name": "Bestiary 2",
                    "link": {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Bestiary 2 pg. 200",
                        "alt": "Bestiary 2 pg. 200",
                        "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq022yq"
                    },
                    "page": 200
                }
            ],
            "html": "Geniekin are mortals whose ancestry has become entangled with that of <a aonid=\"50\" game-obj=\"MonsterFamilies\">genies</a>, causing them to exhibit elemental powers drawn from the Elemental Planes. Though the geniekin found here are all of human descent and have example alignments, geniekin and other planar scions can descend from other ancestries and have any alignment."
        }
    ],
